          <a href="/blog/1841-nested-task-lists" rel="bookmark">Nested task lists</a>\
        </h2>\
\
        <ul class="blog-post-meta">\
    <li class="meta-item">\
      <span class="octicon octicon-calendar"></span>\
      May 14, 2014\
    </li>\
\
  <li class="vcard fn meta-item">\
    <img alt="Matt Todd" class="author-avatar js-avatar" data-user="182" height="18" src="https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/182?s=140" width="18"> <a href="/mtodd">mtodd</a>\
  </li>\
\
    <li class="meta-item">\
      <span class="octicon octicon-file-directory"></span>\
      <a href="/blog/category/ship">New Features</a>\
    </li>\
\
</ul>\
\
\
        <div class="blog-post-body markdown-body">\
          <p>The most organized people know that finishing a task rarely involves just one step. That's why we're excited to announce nested task lists!</p>\
\
<p>For example:</p>\
\
<pre lang="markdown"><code>- [ ] Figure out wormholes\
  - [ ] Call @arfon\
  - [ ] Research ([docs](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wormhole#Time_travel))\
  - [ ] Build prototype #15\
  - [ ] Test run #43 @world-domination/time-travel\
- [ ] ...?\
- [ ] Profit!\
</code></pre>\
\
<p>Now renders as:</p>\
\
<p><a href="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/182/2975762/9aedfb04-db98-11e3-9946-23e06671061f.png" target="_blank"><img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/182/2975762/9aedfb04-db98-11e3-9946-23e06671061f.png" alt="nested task lists" style="max-width:100%;"></a></p>\
\
<p>Updates work as before: check items on and off to update their completion state.</p>\
\
<p>For more information, see the <a href="https://help.github.com/articles/writing-on-github#task-lists">Writing on GitHub</a> article in the GitHub Help.</p>\
        </div>\
      </div>\
